01/06/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The leaders of Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Macedonia and Serbia-Montenegro will meet in Ohrid on Monday (2 June) to discuss preparations for the EU summit in Thessaloniki, Greece later this month.
They are expected to deliver a joint message on the need for clearer perspectives on their countries' integration into the Union.
(Hina, Tanjug, FoNet - 31/05/03;
Makfax, MIA- 30/05/03)
